Threat Hunting Practice – README
📌 Overview

This project demonstrates a basic Threat Hunting workflow using simulated data and lightweight tools. The objective is to identify suspicious activities, validate findings with threat intelligence, and map them to MITRE ATT&CK techniques.

🎯 Objective

To investigate potential unauthorized privilege escalation and validate whether legitimate accounts are being misused.

🧰 Tools Used
Elastic Security (simulated/log reference)
Velociraptor (process query simulation)
AlienVault OTX (threat intelligence lookup)
🔍 Hunting Hypothesis

Unauthorized privilege escalation may occur through misuse of valid domain accounts.

📊 Log Analysis

Event ID 4672 (Special Privileges Assigned) was analyzed.

Timestamp	User	Event ID	Notes
2025-08-18 15:00:00	testuser	4672	Unexpected admin role
🌐 Threat Intelligence

Threat intelligence was gathered using AlienVault OTX.

Technique: T1078 – Valid Accounts
Indicators:
Suspicious IPs linked to credential abuse
Known attack patterns involving privilege escalation
🖥️ Velociraptor Query (Simulated)
SELECT Name, Pid, CommandLine FROM processes;
Findings:
Suspicious process observed: powershell.exe
Unusual execution behavior indicating possible misuse
🧠 Analysis
Event ID 4672 triggered by a non-standard user (testuser)
Indicates possible privilege escalation
Correlated with suspicious process execution
Matches behavior of Valid Account abuse
🧾 Hunting Report (100 Words)

Unauthorized privilege escalation was investigated using Windows Security logs (Event ID 4672). A non-administrative user (“testuser”) was assigned elevated privileges, which deviates from normal behavior. Threat intelligence from AlienVault OTX linked the activity to MITRE ATT&CK technique T1078 (Valid Accounts), suggesting potential credential misuse. Further analysis identified suspicious PowerShell execution under the same user context. Although no confirmed compromise was detected, the activity indicates a potential security risk. Continuous monitoring of privileged accounts and stricter access controls are recommended to prevent unauthorized privilege escalation and misuse of valid credentials.

🛡️ MITRE ATT&CK Mapping
Technique ID	Name	Description
T1078	Valid Accounts	Abuse of legitimate credentials
✅ Conclusion

The investigation highlights the importance of:

Monitoring privileged account activity
Correlating logs with threat intelligence
Detecting misuse of valid credentials
